{{Han compound|米|分|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc|t1=rice}} – [[face powder]] made of [[rice]].

===Etymology 1===
Compare {{cog|my|ဖုန်|t=dust}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

The earliest sense is believed to be "face powder". The term is then used for the color of this powder, "white", and later also the color of a face with this cosmetic, "pink". In early modern Chinese, the ancient "face powder" sense is partly reinforced by {{zh-l|粉底}} (from English {{m|en|foundation}}). {{rfe|zh}}

